content:
The OmniStudio Build Tool includes various tools and processes for troubleshooting, including:

Log Files: Three log files are generated for every command run.

Errors: Review error messages provided by the OmniStudio Build Tool.

Clean Data: The OmniStudio Build Tool includes a script to help find and eliminate incorrect data.

External IDs and Global Keys: Most objects have a field or set of fields used to find unique records. If a deployment finds one object that matches the global key, it overwrites that object during deploy.

Validate Local Data: Use the validateLocalData command to detect missing and duplicate global keys in exported local files.
title: Troubleshooting OmniStudio Build Tool
